# page 18
# EXPENSE RATIO
# In addition to checking average annual rents, you will also be interested in checking the expense ratio between properties
# Also called the operating ratio.  This is the comparison between operating expenses and the rental income.
# The ratio is expresses as a percentage, and it is most valuable when two or more properties are being compared.

* Formula: Expense Ratio
E / I = R
where:
E = operating expenses
I = gross income from rents
R = expense ratio

* Excel Program: Expense Ratio
A1: operating expenses
B1: gross income from rents
C1: =SUM(A1/B1)
